# Cursor Review CLI Project Structure

This is a Node.js CLI tool for AI-powered code reviews with GitHub integration.

## Main Entry Points
- [src/index.js](mdc:src/index.js) - Main CLI entry point
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Project dependencies and scripts

## Architecture
- **Commands**: [src/commands/](mdc:src/commands/) - Individual CLI command implementations
- **Utilities**: [src/utils/](mdc:src/utils/) - Shared utility modules
  - [src/utils/github.js](mdc:src/utils/github.js) - GitHub API integration
  - [src/utils/git.js](mdc:src/utils/git.js) - Git operations
  - [src/utils/state.js](mdc:src/utils/state.js) - State management
  - [src/utils/banner.js](mdc:src/utils/banner.js) - CLI banner/UI

## Command Structure
Each command in [src/commands/](mdc:src/commands/) follows a consistent pattern:
- `config.js` - Configuration management
- `start.js` - Begin review process
- `mark.js` - Mark files as reviewed
- `note.js` - Add review notes
- `status.js` - Show review status
- `verify.js` - Verify review completion
- `finalize.js` - Complete review process
- `reset.js` - Reset review state
